Title: Why is Texas hold 'em so popular? - James McManus
Transcript:
"[{""text"": ""Throughout the 1800s,
in saloons across the West,"", ""start"": 7.295, ""duration"": 3.295}, {""text"": ""you could find cowboys
locked in tense standoffs."", ""start"": 10.59, ""duration"": 3.587}, {""text"": ""But these weren’t shootouts."", ""start"": 14.594, ""duration"": 1.543}, {""text"": ""They were simply playing cards—"", ""start"": 16.137, ""duration"": 1.835}, {""text"": ""for a mountain of chips
worth their weight in gold."", ""start"": 17.972, ""duration"": 3.545}, {""text"": ""Most men wore loaded pistols
in case a player was caught cheating."", ""start"": 22.018, ""duration"": 3.962}, {""text"": ""When they prepared to make
their bets, however,"", ""start"": 26.189, ""duration"": 2.21}, {""text"": ""these cowboys weren’t focused
on their holsters or their cards,"", ""start"": 28.399, ""duration"": 3.754}, {""text"": ""but rather on their opponent’s face."", ""start"": 32.153, ""duration"": 2.461}, {""text"": ""Because not even a bullet could protect
them from a well-executed bluff."", ""start"": 34.822, ""duration"": 4.588}, {""text"": ""From its earliest incarnations,
poker has always been a battle of nerves."", ""start"": 41.287, ""duration"": 4.838}, {""text"": ""The game first emerged around 1800
in the melting pot of New Orleans."", ""start"": 46.292, ""duration"": 4.755}, {""text"": ""At this time, two games
ruled the card tables:"", ""start"": 51.13, ""duration"": 3.212}, {""text"": ""French poque played with a 20-card deck,
and English Brag which used 52-cards."", ""start"": 54.425, ""duration"": 6.799}, {""text"": ""Both these games saw players being dealt
five cards from a four-suit deck,"", ""start"": 61.557, ""duration"": 5.13}, {""text"": ""and then trying to make the best hand
possible according to a simple hierarchy."", ""start"": 66.687, ""duration"": 4.755}, {""text"": ""They would then wager on whether
or not they had the best hand—"", ""start"": 72.11, ""duration"": 3.461}, {""text"": ""either adding more money to the pot"", ""start"": 75.571, ""duration"": 1.835}, {""text"": ""or folding and forfeiting
their chance to win it."", ""start"": 77.406, ""duration"": 2.586}, {""text"": ""But since each player's cards were only
revealed at the end of the hand,"", ""start"": 80.535, ""duration"": 4.17}, {""text"": ""someone with bad cards could always bluff—"", ""start"": 84.705, ""duration"": 2.753}, {""text"": ""betting enough to scare
his opponents into folding."", ""start"": 87.708, ""duration"": 3.254}, {""text"": ""Both games had slightly different hand
combinations, but most importantly,"", ""start"": 91.879, ""duration"": 4.755}, {""text"": ""Brag allowed players to discard
and draw new cards,"", ""start"": 96.676, ""duration"": 3.712}, {""text"": ""making better hands more likely and
allowing for another round of betting."", ""start"": 100.429, ""duration"": 4.714}, {""text"": ""Eventually, the Southerners merged
the two games"", ""start"": 108.437, ""duration"": 2.962}, {""text"": ""into a new version of poque—
which they pronounced pokuh—"", ""start"": 111.399, ""duration"": 3.503}, {""text"": ""that created bigger pots and
opportunities for more complex bluffing."", ""start"": 114.986, ""duration"": 4.838}, {""text"": ""This winning combination of guile, guts,
and gambling caught on quickly."", ""start"": 120.95, ""duration"": 4.546}, {""text"": ""But its popularity skyrocketed
after the invention of the steamboat,"", ""start"": 125.663, ""duration"": 4.421}, {""text"": ""which carried livestock, goods,
and card games"", ""start"": 130.084, ""duration"": 3.045}, {""text"": ""up the Mississippi, Ohio,
and Missouri rivers."", ""start"": 133.129, ""duration"": 2.961}, {""text"": ""By Abraham Lincoln’s election in 1860,"", ""start"": 137.008, ""duration"": 3.17}, {""text"": ""Americans in every state and territory
were playing the newfangled bluffing game."", ""start"": 140.178, ""duration"": 5.463}, {""text"": ""And while many played
for low, friendly stakes,"", ""start"": 145.975, ""duration"": 2.753}, {""text"": ""some gamblers put their homes
and livelihoods on the line."", ""start"": 148.728, ""duration"": 3.879}, {""text"": ""These life-changing bets even found
their way into popular novels"", ""start"": 152.94, ""duration"": 3.879}, {""text"": ""like “Gone with the Wind,”"", ""start"": 156.819, ""duration"": 1.377}, {""text"": ""where Scarlett O’Hara’s father wins
an entire plantation"", ""start"": 158.196, ""duration"": 3.42}, {""text"": ""in a single hand of poker."", ""start"": 161.616, ""duration"": 1.793}, {""text"": ""But as pots became bigger, 
so did the temptation to cheat."", ""start"": 164.911, ""duration"": 3.628}, {""text"": ""Some players enlisted an accomplice
to spy on opponents"", ""start"": 168.664, ""duration"": 3.712}, {""text"": ""and used props to communicate their hands."", ""start"": 172.376, ""duration"": 2.878}, {""text"": ""Others marked important cards with nicks,
dents, or invisible ink."", ""start"": 175.338, ""duration"": 4.754}, {""text"": ""But perhaps the most common method was
sneaking a cold deck into the game."", ""start"": 180.635, ""duration"": 5.171}, {""text"": ""Cold decks were pre-sequenced
to give victims powerful hands"", ""start"": 186.015, ""duration"": 4.379}, {""text"": ""that encouraged them to bet big,"", ""start"": 190.394, ""duration"": 1.961}, {""text"": ""while giving the cheater
an even better one."", ""start"": 192.355, ""duration"": 2.544}, {""text"": ""However, even cheaters had to keep
up with the game’s constant changes."", ""start"": 198.486, ""duration"": 4.296}, {""text"": ""As poker moved west with the Gold Rush,
new variants emerged."", ""start"": 202.865, ""duration"": 4.129}, {""text"": ""Five-card Stud became the game of choice"", ""start"": 207.078, ""duration"": 2.46}, {""text"": ""among notorious gunmen like Doc Holliday,
Wyatt Earp, and Wild Bill Hickok."", ""start"": 209.538, ""duration"": 5.256}, {""text"": ""With four rounds of betting,"", ""start"": 215.336, ""duration"": 1.835}, {""text"": ""Five-card Stud produced
even more lucrative pots,"", ""start"": 217.171, ""duration"": 3.67}, {""text"": ""encouraging so much cheating that
California outlawed the game in 1885."", ""start"": 221.05, ""duration"": 5.714}, {""text"": ""Meanwhile, back in Texas,
another variant emerged"", ""start"": 230.226, ""duration"": 3.336}, {""text"": ""to solve the common problem of having
too many players and not enough cards."", ""start"": 233.562, ""duration"": 4.88}, {""text"": ""This game, known as Texas Hold'em,"", ""start"": 238.943, ""duration"": 2.461}, {""text"": ""became a favorite because its low ratio
of private, hidden cards"", ""start"": 241.404, ""duration"": 4.379}, {""text"": ""to shared, exposed cards"", ""start"": 245.783, ""duration"": 2.085}, {""text"": ""allowed for plenty of deductions
and tactical maneuvering."", ""start"": 247.868, ""duration"": 3.671}, {""text"": ""Even more exciting was no-limit Hold’em,
which allowed players to go all in,"", ""start"": 251.998, ""duration"": 5.255}, {""text"": ""betting everything they had
at any point in the hand."", ""start"": 257.253, ""duration"": 3.378}, {""text"": ""In 1928, Hungarian polymath
John von Neumann"", ""start"": 262.174, ""duration"": 4.213}, {""text"": ""sought to explain the nuances of betting
and bluffing in mathematical terms."", ""start"": 266.387, ""duration"": 4.963}, {""text"": ""His work became the foundation
for a whole new branch of mathematics"", ""start"": 271.559, ""duration"": 4.254}, {""text"": ""called game theory,"", ""start"": 275.813, ""duration"": 1.543}, {""text"": ""which has grown to be vitally important
not only in high-stakes poker,"", ""start"": 277.356, ""duration"": 4.004}, {""text"": ""but in economics and military strategy."", ""start"": 281.444, ""duration"": 2.794}, {""text"": ""In the late 20th century,
game theory became essential"", ""start"": 284.697, ""duration"": 3.211}, {""text"": ""for navigating the geopolitical bluffing
game of nuclear warfare."", ""start"": 287.908, ""duration"": 4.463}, {""text"": ""Today, America’s card game
is an international affair,"", ""start"": 294.415, ""duration"": 3.962}, {""text"": ""attracting players
from over a hundred countries"", ""start"": 298.377, ""duration"": 2.878}, {""text"": ""to the annual World Series of Poker."", ""start"": 301.255, ""duration"": 2.669}, {""text"": ""Fortunes are made and lost every
day on casino floors, poker websites,"", ""start"": 304.383, ""duration"": 5.047}, {""text"": ""and in thousands of live
and online tournaments."", ""start"": 309.43, ""duration"": 3.337}, {""text"": ""So while a single game's outcome
will never be certain,"", ""start"": 312.892, ""duration"": 3.628}, {""text"": ""poker is definitely here to stay."", ""start"": 316.52, ""duration"": 2.628}]"

Title: How to Play Poker
Transcript:
"[{""text"": ""Before you get started playing any type of
5-card poker, you’ll need to learn the 10"", ""start"": 0.28, ""duration"": 5.32}, {""text"": ""basic ways to win."", ""start"": 5.6, ""duration"": 2.73}, {""text"": ""In order from lowest to highest, they are:"", ""start"": 8.33, ""duration"": 4.08}, {""text"": ""1."", ""start"": 12.41, ""duration"": 1.589}, {""text"": ""High card."", ""start"": 13.999, ""duration"": 1.541}, {""text"": ""2."", ""start"": 15.54, ""duration"": 1.16}, {""text"": ""Pair of cards, like two 2s.
3."", ""start"": 16.7, ""duration"": 4.69}, {""text"": ""Two pairs of cards, like two 5s and two 9s.
4."", ""start"": 21.39, ""duration"": 6.24}, {""text"": ""Three of a kind, like three 4s.
5."", ""start"": 27.63, ""duration"": 5.07}, {""text"": ""Straight, which is five cards in sequential
order."", ""start"": 32.7, ""duration"": 5.26}, {""text"": ""For example, a player might have a 3, 4, 5,
6, and 7 of any suit."", ""start"": 37.96, ""duration"": 8.38}, {""text"": ""6."", ""start"": 46.34, ""duration"": 1.499}, {""text"": ""Flush, which is when a player has five cards
of the same suit in any order."", ""start"": 47.839, ""duration"": 5.731}, {""text"": ""For example, a player might have a 2, 7, 10,
Jack, and Queen of spades."", ""start"": 53.57, ""duration"": 9.489}, {""text"": ""7."", ""start"": 63.059, ""duration"": 1.221}, {""text"": ""Full house, which is when a player has a pair
and a three of a kind."", ""start"": 64.28, ""duration"": 6.55}, {""text"": ""8."", ""start"": 70.83, ""duration"": 1.219}, {""text"": ""Four of a kind, like all four Aces."", ""start"": 72.049, ""duration"": 4.331}, {""text"": ""9."", ""start"": 76.38, ""duration"": 1.919}, {""text"": ""Straight flush, which is when you have five
cards in sequential order of the same suit."", ""start"": 78.299, ""duration"": 5.85}, {""text"": ""For example, a player might have a 5, 6, 7,
8, and 9 of clubs."", ""start"": 84.149, ""duration"": 8.591}, {""text"": ""10."", ""start"": 92.74, ""duration"": 1.48}, {""text"": ""Royal Flush, which is a straight flush containing
a 10, Jack, Queen, King, and Ace."", ""start"": 94.22, ""duration"": 14.27}, {""text"": ""If two people have the same hand, the person
with the higher cards wins."", ""start"": 108.49, ""duration"": 5.51}, {""text"": ""So for example, if Daniel has a pair of 3s
and Maggie has a pair of 10s, Maggie wins"", ""start"": 114.0, ""duration"": 8.21}, {""text"": ""because her pair is higher."", ""start"": 122.21, ""duration"": 5.13}, {""text"": ""To play Texas Hold’Em, which is the most
common type of poker, you’ll first need"", ""start"": 127.34, ""duration"": 5.14}, {""text"": ""to bet your “ante,” which is your “buy
in bet” to play the round."", ""start"": 132.48, ""duration"": 6.13}, {""text"": ""The ante is usually a small bet, like $1 or
$5, and it’s decided by the table."", ""start"": 138.61, ""duration"": 8.87}, {""text"": ""Once everyone has their ante, the dealer will
deal two cards to each player."", ""start"": 147.48, ""duration"": 5.81}, {""text"": ""Keep these cards secret from everyone else."", ""start"": 153.29, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""Now, every player will take a look at their
cards and choose whether or not to bet."", ""start"": 156.59, ""duration"": 8.07}, {""text"": ""Whenever there’s a betting round, you can
choose to “fold,” which means not playing"", ""start"": 164.66, ""duration"": 5.109}, {""text"": ""this round, “check,” which means matching
their bet, or “raise,” which means adding"", ""start"": 169.769, ""duration"": 8.021}, {""text"": ""more money to the betting pool."", ""start"": 177.79, ""duration"": 5.1}, {""text"": ""Players that are unwilling to “check”
a bet have to fold; and if everyone but one"", ""start"": 182.89, ""duration"": 5.39}, {""text"": ""player “folds,” that player wins!"", ""start"": 188.28, ""duration"": 4.65}, {""text"": ""Once everyone has bet, the dealer will reveal
three cards."", ""start"": 192.93, ""duration"": 5.559}, {""text"": ""These cards are known as the “flop.”"", ""start"": 198.489, ""duration"": 3.991}, {""text"": ""When you see the flop, start planning what
hand you want to make, keeping in mind that"", ""start"": 202.48, ""duration"": 5.6}, {""text"": ""there are still two more cards to be revealed."", ""start"": 208.08, ""duration"": 3.379}, {""text"": ""For example, you might want to aim for a flush,
which is when you have five cards of the same"", ""start"": 211.459, ""duration"": 7.261}, {""text"": ""suit."", ""start"": 218.72, ""duration"": 4.09}, {""text"": ""After the flop, everyone has the chance to
bet again, before the dealer reveals the next"", ""start"": 222.81, ""duration"": 7.44}, {""text"": ""card, which is the “turn.”"", ""start"": 230.25, ""duration"": 5.849}, {""text"": ""Bet again if you want to, then the dealer
will reveal the “river,” which is the"", ""start"": 236.099, ""duration"": 7.47}, {""text"": ""last card."", ""start"": 243.569, ""duration"": 2.84}, {""text"": ""At this point, you’ll see a total of 7 cards:
two in your hands, and five on the table."", ""start"": 246.409, ""duration"": 9.351}, {""text"": ""Now, players will bet once last time, then
everyone will reveal their hand."", ""start"": 255.76, ""duration"": 13.43}, {""text"": ""Your goal is to create the highest hand possible
out of those seven cards, even if it means"", ""start"": 269.19, ""duration"": 6.199}, {""text"": ""only using one card from your hand and four
cards from the table."", ""start"": 275.389, ""duration"": 8.761}, {""text"": ""The player with the best hand wins!"", ""start"": 284.15, ""duration"": 2.85}]"

Title: Poker Rules and Etiquette for Beginners | PokerStars Learn
Transcript:
"[{""text"": ""Hi, welcome to PokerStars Learn."", ""start"": 0.0, ""duration"": 1.6}, {""text"": ""I'm James Hartigan, and this is
our guide to 'Poker Rules and Etiquette.'"", ""start"": 1.65, ""duration"": 4.079}, {""text"": ""After watching this video,"", ""start"": 5.779, ""duration"": 1.221}, {""text"": ""you'll have a greater understanding
of the rules of the game..."", ""start"": 7.1, ""duration"": 2.1}, {""text"": ""and what's expected of you at the
table."", ""start"": 9.35, ""duration"": 1.923}, {""text"": ""Now, if you're totally new to poker,"", ""start"": 11.323, ""duration"": 1.677}, {""text"": ""you might want to start with our
'How to Play Poker' video,"", ""start"": 13.05, ""duration"": 2.976}, {""text"": ""because this guide assumes you know
the basics. And of course,"", ""start"": 16.076, ""duration"": 2.724}, {""text"": ""for all the best poker content
and more tutorials..."", ""start"": 18.8, ""duration"": 2.4}, {""text"": ""don't forget to hit the subscribe
button."", ""start"": 21.2, ""duration"": 2.0}, {""text"": ""Let's start with how you would
deal a poker game."", ""start"": 26.0, ""duration"": 2.4}, {""text"": ""If you play online or at a casino,
you don't have to worry about dealing,"", ""start"": 29.3, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""but if you're playing privately
with friends, it's customary..."", ""start"": 32.4, ""duration"": 2.9}, {""text"": ""that the player with the Dealer
Button actually deals the hand."", ""start"": 35.3, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""Take the deck of cards and shuffle
them all facedown."", ""start"": 38.45, ""duration"": 3.617}, {""text"": ""Any good shuffle is okay,"", ""start"": 42.117, ""duration"": 1.283}, {""text"": ""assuming it mixes up the deck and
nobody sees any of the cards."", ""start"": 43.4, ""duration"": 3.2}, {""text"": ""Then, cut the deck in two and move
the lower half to the top."", ""start"": 46.6, ""duration"": 4.5}, {""text"": ""This is known as cutting the cards."", ""start"": 51.1, ""duration"": 1.9}, {""text"": ""It's an added security measure
to prevent anyone from manipulating..."", ""start"": 53.0, ""duration"": 3.8}, {""text"": ""the cards while shuffling them."", ""start"": 56.85, ""duration"": 1.503}, {""text"": ""Next, deal to the player to the immediate 
left of the button - the small blind -"", ""start"": 58.403, ""duration"": 4.297}, {""text"": ""and then work in a clockwise direction,
ending with yourself."", ""start"": 62.9, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""Continue dealing until you've dealt
two cards facedown to every player."", ""start"": 66.5, ""duration"": 4.5}, {""text"": ""We then have the pre-flop betting
round."", ""start"": 71.55, ""duration"": 2.804}, {""text"": ""Couple of notes..."", ""start"": 74.454, ""duration"": 1.148}, {""text"": ""In a tournament, a player has to be
 at their seat when the..."", ""start"": 75.702, ""duration"": 3.09}, {""text"": ""last card is dealt to take part 
 in the hand;"", ""start"": 78.942, ""duration"": 2.43}, {""text"": ""Hole cards are dealt to every position
 at the table regardless,"", ""start"": 81.422, ""duration"": 2.678}, {""text"": ""but if a player hasn't taken their
seat before the last card is dealt,"", ""start"": 84.15, ""duration"": 3.839}, {""text"": ""the hand is automatically 
mucked, or folded;"", ""start"": 88.139, ""duration"": 3.012}, {""text"": ""In a cash game, a player won't
 be dealt any cards..."", ""start"": 91.251, ""duration"": 3.39}, {""text"": ""if they're not at the table."", ""start"": 94.691, ""duration"": 1.209}, {""text"": ""After the first betting round is
complete,"", ""start"": 96.25, ""duration"": 2.138}, {""text"": ""you're going to deal the flop."", ""start"": 98.488, ""duration"": 1.791}, {""text"": ""To do this, simply discard the card
 on the top of the deck."", ""start"": 100.329, ""duration"": 3.971}, {""text"": ""Then deal the next three cards
face-up in the middle of the table."", ""start"": 104.4, ""duration"": 3.6}, {""text"": ""Why discard that top card?"", ""start"": 108.8, ""duration"": 2.1}, {""text"": ""'Burning' a card prevents any players
 knowing what's coming next,"", ""start"": 110.95, ""duration"": 2.832}, {""text"": ""in the unlikely event that the card on the top
 of the deck has become marked."", ""start"": 113.882, ""duration"": 4.446}, {""text"": ""It helps protect the integrity
 of the game."", ""start"": 118.428, ""duration"": 2.165}, {""text"": ""When dealing the turn, you also 
burn a card before dealing..."", ""start"": 120.693, ""duration"": 2.834}, {""text"": ""one card face-up to the right 
of the flop."", ""start"": 123.627, ""duration"": 2.639}, {""text"": ""And same again with the river."", ""start"": 126.366, ""duration"": 1.635}, {""text"": ""Burn a card and deal the final 
community card..."", ""start"": 128.16, ""duration"": 1.841}, {""text"": ""face-up to the right of the turn
card."", ""start"": 130.85, ""duration"": 2.243}, {""text"": ""So, that's the basics of dealing."", ""start"": 133.143, ""duration"": 1.957}, {""text"": ""Now, let's talk about how to
 handle your hole cards."", ""start"": 135.2, ""duration"": 3.362}, {""text"": ""First, it's important you don't show
 them to anyone else..."", ""start"": 138.612, ""duration"": 2.388}, {""text"": ""while the hand is in progress. 
Your hole cards are private."", ""start"": 141.05, ""duration"": 2.822}, {""text"": ""Shield them when you look at them 
to prevent the players either..."", ""start"": 143.972, ""duration"": 2.892}, {""text"": ""side of you, or anyone standing 
behind you, from seeing them."", ""start"": 146.914, ""duration"": 3.586}, {""text"": ""Players usually peel the corners 
of their cards up with one hand..."", ""start"": 150.6, ""duration"": 3.656}, {""text"": ""and shield with the other."", ""start"": 154.306, ""duration"": 1.494}, {""text"": ""You can look at your hand at any
time, or you don't have to look at all,"", ""start"": 156.2, ""duration"": 3.5}, {""text"": ""but you probably should."", ""start"": 159.8, ""duration"": 1.49}, {""text"": ""Second, while playing a hand 
it's good practice to protect..."", ""start"": 161.39, ""duration"": 3.08}, {""text"": ""your hole cards from being 
accidentally mucked by the dealer,"", ""start"": 164.52, ""duration"": 3.08}, {""text"": ""by keeping them close to you, and
either resting your hand on..."", ""start"": 167.7, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""the cards or putting a single chip
on top of them."", ""start"": 170.7, ""duration"": 2.8}, {""text"": ""If your hole cards are too far forward, 
the dealer may think you folded,"", ""start"": 173.6, ""duration"": 4.0}, {""text"": ""and sweep your cards into the muck."", ""start"": 177.65, ""duration"": 2.75}, {""text"": ""If this happens, it's considered to
 be your mistake."", ""start"": 180.5, ""duration"": 3.513}, {""text"": ""It's highly unlikely you'll get your hole
 cards back and you'll be out of the hand."", ""start"": 184.063, ""duration"": 4.237}, {""text"": ""Finally, when protecting your cards
don't hide them from view."", ""start"": 188.3, ""duration"": 3.9}, {""text"": ""For example, don't place your 
chips in front of them."", ""start"": 192.25, ""duration"": 2.55}, {""text"": ""This might confuse the players
and the dealer about whether..."", ""start"": 194.95, ""duration"": 2.15}, {""text"": ""you're still in the hand."", ""start"": 197.15, ""duration"": 1.05}, {""text"": ""It could even be viewed as 
an underhand tactic:"", ""start"": 198.2, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""A way of trying to stay in the
hand without betting,"", ""start"": 201.25, ""duration"": 2.658}, {""text"": ""and moves like this are referred
 to as 'angle shooting.'"", ""start"": 203.958, ""duration"": 3.342}, {""text"": ""Another thing to mention is that
if you're folding, you can't..."", ""start"": 207.6, ""duration"": 3.2}, {""text"": ""just show one player your hole
cards."", ""start"": 210.85, ""duration"": 2.188}, {""text"": ""Casinos generally employ a 
'show one, show all' policy..."", ""start"": 213.138, ""duration"": 3.456}, {""text"": ""in the interest of fairness for
 all players."", ""start"": 216.694, ""duration"": 2.666}, {""text"": ""Finally, after you folded don't announce
 your cards to anyone..."", ""start"": 219.46, ""duration"": 3.485}, {""text"": ""while there's still a hand in progress."", ""start"": 222.995, ""duration"": 1.405}, {""text"": ""Imagine a situation where you make
a trivial fold with Jack-Three,"", ""start"": 224.6, ""duration"": 3.4}, {""text"": ""and the flop comes Jack-Three-Three."", ""start"": 228.2, ""duration"": 2.5}, {""text"": ""You might be frustrated or amused
by the situation, but keep it to yourself."", ""start"": 231.5, ""duration"": 5.3}, {""text"": ""If you're not in the hand you shouldn't
do or say anything..."", ""start"": 237.15, ""duration"": 3.479}, {""text"": ""that might influence play."", ""start"": 240.679, ""duration"": 1.421}, {""text"": ""Let's talk about the times when
you will be showing your hole cards."", ""start"": 242.1, ""duration"": 3.5}, {""text"": ""In our 'How to Play Poker' video, 
we explained how players will..."", ""start"": 247.05, ""duration"": 3.25}, {""text"": ""reveal their cards at showdown,
after the final betting round."", ""start"": 250.35, ""duration"": 3.45}, {""text"": ""The player whose bet has been called, 
the aggressor, is expected to show first."", ""start"": 254.2, ""duration"": 3.803}, {""text"": ""In a live game, the second player
 doesn't have to show..."", ""start"": 258.878, ""duration"": 3.233}, {""text"": ""if they can't beat their 
opponent's hand."", ""start"": 262.161, ""duration"": 2.039}, {""text"": ""If there was no bet on the river,
the player to the left of the..."", ""start"": 264.5, ""duration"": 2.8}, {""text"": ""dealer shows first, and then it
goes in order clockwise."", ""start"": 267.3, ""duration"": 2.6}, {""text"": ""There is one exception to this."", ""start"": 270.0, ""duration"": 1.4}, {""text"": ""If you have an unbeatable hand,
known in poker as the 'nuts,'"", ""start"": 272.05, ""duration"": 4.055}, {""text"": ""or the near nuts, you shouldn't wait."", ""start"": 276.155, ""duration"": 2.345}, {""text"": ""This is known as slow-rolling, and
is poor etiquette towards..."", ""start"": 278.75, ""duration"": 2.479}, {""text"": ""your fellow players. 
Show both cards immediately."", ""start"": 281.279, ""duration"": 3.421}, {""text"": ""Now, if there's a player who's gone
all-in earlier in the hand..."", ""start"": 284.8, ""duration"": 3.2}, {""text"": ""and another player has called, providing
there's no one else involved,"", ""start"": 288.05, ""duration"": 3.185}, {""text"": ""both players turn the hole cards 
face-up before any remaining..."", ""start"": 291.385, ""duration"": 3.338}, {""text"": ""community cards are dealt."", ""start"": 294.823, ""duration"": 1.213}, {""text"": ""One word of advice."", ""start"": 296.086, ""duration"": 1.214}, {""text"": ""If you're involved in an all-in
situation, don't reveal your cards too early."", ""start"": 297.7, ""duration"": 4.7}, {""text"": ""Please wait for the dealer to confirm
that the action has closed,"", ""start"": 302.55, ""duration"": 3.237}, {""text"": ""and there are no more bets."", ""start"": 305.887, ""duration"": 1.528}, {""text"": ""If you're too quick, you could lose some calls,"", ""start"": 307.515, ""duration"": 3.167}, {""text"": ""or worse, gain some calls 
from dominating hands."", ""start"": 310.732, ""duration"": 2.768}, {""text"": ""Right, let's move on from
 cards to chips."", ""start"": 313.5, ""duration"": 2.7}, {""text"": ""For as long as you're playing at
the table you will have a stack"", ""start"": 317.9, ""duration"": 2.7}, {""text"": ""of chips in front of you."", ""start"": 320.6, ""duration"": 1.3}, {""text"": ""You might see players shuffling
or riffling their chips, but..."", ""start"": 322.3, ""duration"": 2.7}, {""text"": ""chips must stay on the table
at all times for everyone to see."", ""start"": 325.0, ""duration"": 4.1}, {""text"": ""Players need to make decisions
based on how many chips their..."", ""start"": 329.7, ""duration"": 2.7}, {""text"": ""opponents have."", ""start"": 332.5, ""duration"": 0.872}, {""text"": ""A couple of notes related to this."", ""start"": 333.422, ""duration"": 1.378}, {""text"": ""You must make sure your higher-value
chips are visible."", ""start"": 335.05, ""duration"": 3.059}, {""text"": ""For example, if you had a stack of 1000s
 behind a stack of 25s,"", ""start"": 338.209, ""duration"": 4.622}, {""text"": ""it could be judged that you 
were intentionally..."", ""start"": 342.881, ""duration"": 2.619}, {""text"": ""trying to hide them to trick players,"", ""start"": 345.5, ""duration"": 2.0}, {""text"": ""and you could receive a penalty."", ""start"": 347.85, ""duration"": 1.432}, {""text"": ""For the benefit of the dealer and
 other players, it's good..."", ""start"": 349.332, ""duration"": 2.668}, {""text"": ""practice to keep your chips in
countable stacks."", ""start"": 352.05, ""duration"": 2.51}, {""text"": ""Ideally, level stacks of 20, with
 your highest value chips at the front."", ""start"": 354.61, ""duration"": 5.019}, {""text"": ""As a tournament progresses
 and the blinds increase,"", ""start"": 359.729, ""duration"": 2.848}, {""text"": ""low value chips are removed from play
 when they're no longer needed."", ""start"": 362.627, ""duration"": 3.573}, {""text"": ""The dealer organizes this and replaces
them with higher value chips."", ""start"": 366.45, ""duration"": 3.504}, {""text"": ""For example, four 25s can 
be traded for one 100."", ""start"": 370.004, ""duration"": 4.096}, {""text"": ""This is called coloring up."", ""start"": 374.25, ""duration"": 2.143}, {""text"": ""In a situation where there are 
odd chips -"", ""start"": 376.493, ""duration"": 2.062}, {""text"": ""for example, four players at the
 table each have a single 25 -"", ""start"": 378.605, ""duration"": 3.119}, {""text"": ""the dealer will run a chip race."", ""start"": 381.774, ""duration"": 1.926}, {""text"": ""They will deal a single card to
these four players with the..."", ""start"": 383.95, ""duration"": 3.245}, {""text"": ""highest card earning the 100 chip."", ""start"": 387.245, ""duration"": 2.055}, {""text"": ""This isn't going to impact your
tournament life at all, but it..."", ""start"": 389.3, ""duration"": 2.9}, {""text"": ""does explain where your single
green chip went while you..."", ""start"": 392.2, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""were on break."", ""start"": 395.3, ""duration"": 0.685}, {""text"": ""When it comes to betting your chips,"", ""start"": 396.035, ""duration"": 1.665}, {""text"": ""you must be aware of string-betting
and avoid doing it."", ""start"": 397.8, ""duration"": 3.9}, {""text"": ""String-betting is making a single bet
in several actions."", ""start"": 401.7, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""A classic example is the movie cliché..."", ""start"": 405.1, ""duration"": 2.4}, {""text"": ""where the villain says
""I call your 1,000,"" - throws a 1,000 chip -"", ""start"": 407.7, ""duration"": 4.5}, {""text"": """"and I raise you 5,000."""", ""start"": 412.3, ""duration"": 2.0}, {""text"": ""This doesn't happen in real life.
It's actually against the rules."", ""start"": 414.4, ""duration"": 2.9}, {""text"": ""You must put your bet forward in
a single motion."", ""start"": 417.55, ""duration"": 3.586}, {""text"": ""Alternatively, you can verbally announce 
your bet. That becomes binding."", ""start"": 421.236, ""duration"": 3.373}, {""text"": ""So you can say ""Raise 5,000,""
 and then you can take your time..."", ""start"": 424.659, ""duration"": 4.741}, {""text"": ""counting out your chips and putting
them out one at a time."", ""start"": 429.45, ""duration"": 2.264}, {""text"": ""One time when it's really important
 to announce your bet..."", ""start"": 431.814, ""duration"": 2.081}, {""text"": ""is when you are raising with one chip."", ""start"": 434.145, ""duration"": 3.255}, {""text"": ""In a casino, throwing one chip into
the middle without saying..."", ""start"": 437.8, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""anything is always a call."", ""start"": 441.15, ""duration"": 2.093}, {""text"": ""Inexperienced players are often caught 
out by this when they're trying..."", ""start"": 443.343, ""duration"": 2.543}, {""text"": ""to raise with a single chip but fail to
 verbally announce it."", ""start"": 445.986, ""duration"": 3.986}, {""text"": ""This rule applies for both larger 
and smaller chips."", ""start"": 450.022, ""duration"": 2.978}, {""text"": ""If there's a bet of 100 and you
put in a 500 chip, it's a call of a 100."", ""start"": 453.4, ""duration"": 5.6}, {""text"": ""If you put in a 25 chip
by mistake, it's still a call of 100."", ""start"": 459.2, ""duration"": 3.8}, {""text"": ""And if you place two or more chips
 into the pot in a single motion..."", ""start"": 463.85, ""duration"": 3.95}, {""text"": ""without saying anything you are likely 
to be held to a raise."", ""start"": 467.9, ""duration"": 3.813}, {""text"": ""Here's an example. 
Your opponent bets 225."", ""start"": 471.863, ""duration"": 3.875}, {""text"": ""You want to call but you don't
 have any 100 chips."", ""start"": 475.788, ""duration"": 3.112}, {""text"": ""You want to make life easy for
the dealer,"", ""start"": 479.2, ""duration"": 1.8}, {""text"": ""so you put in a 1000 chip and a
25, so you can get 800 in change."", ""start"": 481.1, ""duration"": 5.9}, {""text"": ""Unless you say the word call before
putting in those chips..."", ""start"": 487.0, ""duration"": 3.6}, {""text"": ""It could be ruled that you have
raised to 1,025."", ""start"": 490.85, ""duration"": 4.477}, {""text"": ""Ultimately, it's good practice 
to announce all your bets clearly,"", ""start"": 495.427, ""duration"": 3.475}, {""text"": ""while you’re getting comfortable with 
handling chips,"", ""start"": 499.002, ""duration"": 2.049}, {""text"": ""and to keep your chips in clear view 
and easily countable."", ""start"": 501.151, ""duration"": 3.763}, {""text"": ""In the next section, we're going to
 cover the general etiquette..."", ""start"": 505.064, ""duration"": 3.462}, {""text"": ""of players at the table."", ""start"": 508.626, ""duration"": 1.715}, {""text"": ""First of all,"", ""start"": 510.391, ""duration"": 1.009}, {""text"": ""you should always be respectful
of your fellow players and the dealer."", ""start"": 511.65, ""duration"": 4.344}, {""text"": ""Players who don't will receive
 a warning and may be..."", ""start"": 515.006, ""duration"": 3.394}, {""text"": ""asked to leave the casino."", ""start"": 518.5, ""duration"": 0.506}, {""text"": ""If you're in a multi-way pot -a hand..."", ""start"": 519.942, ""duration"": 2.064}, {""text"": ""with three or more players - then
you can't say anything that could..."", ""start"": 522.006, ""duration"": 3.994}, {""text"": ""be seen to influence the actions
of the other players."", ""start"": 526.05, ""duration"": 2.783}, {""text"": ""This is relaxed when only two players
 are in the hand, at which point..."", ""start"": 528.883, ""duration"": 3.317}, {""text"": ""those players are free to say almost
anything they like."", ""start"": 532.25, ""duration"": 3.188}, {""text"": ""Another issue is when players 
act out of turn."", ""start"": 535.488, ""duration"": 3.312}, {""text"": ""A lot of the times it's done by mistake,
when players aren't paying attention."", ""start"": 538.8, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""But it's considered unsporting and 
disrespectful, and can result in..."", ""start"": 542.45, ""duration"": 4.339}, {""text"": ""players being penalized. 
Just wait for your turn."", ""start"": 546.839, ""duration"": 3.461}, {""text"": ""Using a phone at the table during
a hand is forbidden in a casino."", ""start"": 550.3, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""You're also not allowed to take
a phone call at the table, whether..."", ""start"": 553.7, ""duration"": 2.7}, {""text"": ""you're in a hand or not."", ""start"": 556.45, ""duration"": 1.35}, {""text"": ""You shouldn't have your phone on 
the surface of the table either."", ""start"": 557.9, ""duration"": 2.738}, {""text"": ""In fact, there shouldn't be..."", ""start"": 560.688, ""duration"": 1.112}, {""text"": ""anything on the playing surface
other than your chips and cards."", ""start"": 561.8, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""As for listening to music, that's
okay, as long as you use headphones."", ""start"": 565.35, ""duration"": 3.395}, {""text"": ""Just make sure you can still keep
track of what's happening at the table."", ""start"": 568.795, ""duration"": 3.405}, {""text"": ""You can also wear a hood, wear
a hat, wear sunglasses. All fine."", ""start"": 572.25, ""duration"": 3.85}, {""text"": ""Finally,"", ""start"": 576.15, ""duration"": 0.25}, {""text"": ""you can take your time when playing
a hand within reason."", ""start"": 576.45, ""duration"": 3.927}, {""text"": ""In tournaments, the blind levels 
increase at regular intervals."", ""start"": 580.427, ""duration"": 2.873}, {""text"": ""So taking 15 minutes over a decision
in a game with 20 minute..."", ""start"": 583.45, ""duration"": 3.603}, {""text"": ""blind levels will agitate other players."", ""start"": 587.503, ""duration"": 2.697}, {""text"": ""Players may 'call the clock' and
ask the tournament director to put..."", ""start"": 590.35, ""duration"": 3.196}, {""text"": ""a time limit on your decision."", ""start"": 593.646, ""duration"": 2.152}, {""text"": ""Also, many tournaments now play with 
a shot clock giving players a fixed amount..."", ""start"": 595.898, ""duration"": 4.176}, {""text"": ""of time for each action on
 each betting street."", ""start"": 600.174, ""duration"": 2.635}, {""text"": ""The most important takeaway from this
 is to be respectful and be alert."", ""start"": 602.909, ""duration"": 4.834}, {""text"": ""So, now you know the general 
rules of playing poker,"", ""start"": 607.793, ""duration"": 3.707}, {""text"": ""and you're ready for your game."", ""start"": 611.65, ""duration"": 1.95}, {""text"": ""I'm James Hartigan. This has been the 
guide to 'Poker Rules..."", ""start"": 613.7, ""duration"": 2.622}, {""text"": ""and Etiquette from PokerStars."", ""start"": 616.422, ""duration"": 1.812}, {""text"": ""Please, don't forget to like this video
 and subscribe for more poker content."", ""start"": 618.334, ""duration"": 4.188}, {""text"": ""Thanks for watching."", ""start"": 622.572, ""duration"": 0.928}]"

Title: How To Bet In Poker | PokerStars Learn
Transcript:
"[{""text"": ""Hello, I'm James Hartigan. 
Welcome to PokerStars Learn,"", ""start"": 0.35, ""duration"": 2.855}, {""text"": ""and our guide to 'Betting and 
Raising in Texas Hold'em.'"", ""start"": 3.355, ""duration"": 3.486}, {""text"": ""Betting in a poker hand is any 
action where you put chips into the pot."", ""start"": 6.891, ""duration"": 3.509}, {""text"": ""By the end of this video, you will 
know the basics of why, when,"", ""start"": 10.75, ""duration"": 3.45}, {""text"": ""and how much to bet."", ""start"": 14.3, ""duration"": 1.175}, {""text"": ""There are three different ways you
 can put chips into the pot:"", ""start"": 15.575, ""duration"": 3.045}, {""text"": ""Making the initial bet, calling
 that bet, or raising it."", ""start"": 18.67, ""duration"": 3.63}, {""text"": ""This video is going to focus on
the more active or aggressive options:"", ""start"": 22.35, ""duration"": 4.181}, {""text"": ""Betting and raising."", ""start"": 26.581, ""duration"": 1.419}, {""text"": ""If you want to learn more about
poker, please don't forget..."", ""start"": 28.45, ""duration"": 2.117}, {""text"": ""to subscribe to this channel."", ""start"": 30.617, ""duration"": 1.283}, {""text"": ""Okay, let's start by going over
the basics of betting..."", ""start"": 35.0, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""If nobody else has entered the
pot, then you can bet first."", ""start"": 38.35, ""duration"": 3.126}, {""text"": ""That could be the minimum - the 
current value of the big blind - or more."", ""start"": 41.526, ""duration"": 3.874}, {""text"": ""If another player has already bet,
then you can add..."", ""start"": 45.95, ""duration"": 2.715}, {""text"": ""the same number of chips to call,
or you can raise."", ""start"": 48.765, ""duration"": 3.099}, {""text"": ""The minimum raise will be
 double the size of the current bet,"", ""start"": 51.914, ""duration"": 3.386}, {""text"": ""but you can make it more."", ""start"": 55.3, ""duration"": 1.4}, {""text"": ""So why put in a bet? Broadly speaking,
there are two primary reasons:"", ""start"": 57.0, ""duration"": 5.0}, {""text"": ""the first is to bet for value, 
the second is to bet as a bluff."", ""start"": 62.25, ""duration"": 4.85}, {""text"": ""If you think you’ve got the best hand,
 you want to build a pot,"", ""start"": 67.1, ""duration"": 2.85}, {""text"": ""and therefore win more chips."", ""start"": 70.1, ""duration"": 1.596}, {""text"": ""This type of bet is called
 a 'value bet.'"", ""start"": 71.746, ""duration"": 2.654}, {""text"": ""You’re betting hoping to get called
 by an opponent with a worse hand."", ""start"": 74.45, ""duration"": 4.2}, {""text"": ""But you can't always rely on having
the best hand to win, though."", ""start"": 78.9, ""duration"": 2.8}, {""text"": ""The other reason to bet is when
you know you don't have the best hand."", ""start"": 82.1, ""duration"": 3.6}, {""text"": ""You want to make your opponent
think that you do,"", ""start"": 85.95, ""duration"": 2.258}, {""text"": ""you want them to fold."", ""start"": 88.308, ""duration"": 1.53}, {""text"": ""This type of bet is famously 
known as a bluff."", ""start"": 89.888, ""duration"": 3.112}, {""text"": ""It's the opposite of a value bet."", ""start"": 93.2, ""duration"": 1.4}, {""text"": ""You're betting hoping to get
your opponent to fold a better hand."", ""start"": 94.7, ""duration"": 4.2}, {""text"": ""While bluffing is central to poker, 
it's only part of the game."", ""start"": 98.95, ""duration"": 3.208}, {""text"": ""You should be very selective, 
only bluffing when you're confident..."", ""start"": 102.258, ""duration"": 3.831}, {""text"": ""it will work. For example, against tight,
 risk-averse players,"", ""start"": 106.139, ""duration"": 3.761}, {""text"": ""and preferably when your hand still
has a chance of improving..."", ""start"": 110.15, ""duration"": 2.928}, {""text"": ""on the turn or river."", ""start"": 113.178, ""duration"": 1.559}, {""text"": ""So, now you know why
 you want to bet,"", ""start"": 114.787, ""duration"": 2.313}, {""text"": ""let's walk through the different
betting round in a hand of Hold'em."", ""start"": 117.3, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""You can't be first into the pot
before the flop, because the.."", ""start"": 122.1, ""duration"": 2.5}, {""text"": ""players in the small blind and the 
big blind will have already.."", ""start"": 124.65, ""duration"": 2.776}, {""text"": ""posted the first bets."", ""start"": 127.526, ""duration"": 0.475}, {""text"": ""So here, you're going to be raising."", ""start"": 128.517, ""duration"": 1.883}, {""text"": ""The question is: How much to raise?"", ""start"": 130.65, ""duration"": 2.05}, {""text"": ""Well, it's best to stick to a standard
 raise size for all of your hands -"", ""start"": 132.8, ""duration"": 5.129}, {""text"": ""somewhere between two big blinds 
and three big blinds -"", ""start"": 137.979, ""duration"": 2.621}, {""text"": ""you don't want to give away the
strength of the cards you're holding."", ""start"": 140.75, ""duration"": 3.118}, {""text"": ""What you must not do is bet based
 on the value of your hole cards."", ""start"": 143.968, ""duration"": 4.352}, {""text"": ""For example, don't raise less
 with King-Queen suited..."", ""start"": 148.37, ""duration"": 2.63}, {""text"": ""than you would with Aces."", ""start"": 151.1, ""duration"": 2.0}, {""text"": ""If you reveal these hands at showdown
after the last betting round,"", ""start"": 153.4, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""your opponents will immediately
make the connection..."", ""start"": 156.75, ""duration"": 2.256}, {""text"": ""and they'll use that information 
against you in later rounds."", ""start"": 159.056, ""duration"": 3.244}, {""text"": ""3-betting is the more common
name for re-raising before the flop."", ""start"": 163.6, ""duration"": 4.3}, {""text"": ""It means to put in the third bet.
Think of it this way."", ""start"": 167.9, ""duration"": 3.7}, {""text"": ""The big blind is the first bet,"", ""start"": 172.1, ""duration"": 1.9}, {""text"": ""the initial raise is the second
bet, and the re-raise is the 3-bet."", ""start"": 174.2, ""duration"": 3.9}, {""text"": ""You'll also hear about 4-betting 
and 5-betting, which..."", ""start"": 178.1, ""duration"": 4.1}, {""text"": ""is re-re-raising and
 re-re-re-raising."", ""start"": 182.25, ""duration"": 4.483}, {""text"": ""And now you know why it's easier
 to use numbers."", ""start"": 187.033, ""duration"": 2.475}, {""text"": ""Obviously, you can re-raise for
 value or as a bluff."", ""start"": 189.608, ""duration"": 3.065}, {""text"": ""So, if a player at the table calls
 your raise - or re-raise -"", ""start"": 192.773, ""duration"": 3.327}, {""text"": ""you're now going to see a flop."", ""start"": 196.35, ""duration"": 2.225}, {""text"": ""And as the preflop aggressor,
the last person to raise,"", ""start"": 198.675, ""duration"": 3.147}, {""text"": ""you're  expected to make a 
continuation bet."", ""start"": 201.872, ""duration"": 2.528}, {""text"": ""Continuation betting, commonly
known as C-betting is where the..."", ""start"": 205.7, ""duration"": 3.5}, {""text"": ""player who made the final raise
in the previous betting round..."", ""start"": 209.2, ""duration"": 2.6}, {""text"": ""is the first player to bet
in the next round."", ""start"": 211.8, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""Players often check to the aggressor,
expecting them to bet."", ""start"": 215.35, ""duration"": 4.114}, {""text"": ""C-betting for value works because
 if you connect with the flop,"", ""start"": 219.564, ""duration"": 2.81}, {""text"": ""or you think you still have the 
best hand,"", ""start"": 222.474, ""duration"": 2.243}, {""text"": ""it's time to build that pot."", ""start"": 224.817, ""duration"": 1.435}, {""text"": ""C-betting as a bluff also works because
 even if you haven't connected..."", ""start"": 226.352, ""duration"": 3.729}, {""text"": ""with the board, 
you can pretend you have."", ""start"": 230.131, ""duration"": 2.269}, {""text"": ""Let's say there's an Ace on the
flop and you don't have an Ace."", ""start"": 232.65, ""duration"": 3.735}, {""text"": ""You can bet here, hoping to convince
 your opponent you do have it."", ""start"": 236.435, ""duration"": 3.465}, {""text"": ""Remember: you raised before the
flop, and a lot of the hands you're..."", ""start"": 240.0, ""duration"": 3.7}, {""text"": ""likely to have done this with 
include an Ace."", ""start"": 243.8, ""duration"": 2.943}, {""text"": ""But you shouldn't be mindlessly 
C-bet bluffing on every single flop."", ""start"": 246.793, ""duration"": 3.607}, {""text"": ""The best times to do it are when
there are no obvious draws,"", ""start"": 250.5, ""duration"": 2.8}, {""text"": ""and when there are very few players
involved in the pot."", ""start"": 253.45, ""duration"": 3.014}, {""text"": ""It's worth highlighting it isn't compulsory
 to C-bet and checking is not off-limits."", ""start"": 256.003, ""duration"": 6.994}, {""text"": ""Now, let's switch things around."", ""start"": 262.154, ""duration"": 1.946}, {""text"": ""If you're the player who called
the original raise, you can take..."", ""start"": 265.7, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""the initiative to bet first after the flop
 rather than checking to the aggressor."", ""start"": 269.0, ""duration"": 4.2}, {""text"": ""This is called 'donk-betting' because
inexperienced players..."", ""start"": 273.25, ""duration"": 2.317}, {""text"": ""might do it without thinking. But that 
doesn't mean it's a bad thing."", ""start"": 276.267, ""duration"": 3.225}, {""text"": ""In situations where there are multiple
 players in the pot,"", ""start"": 279.592, ""duration"": 2.674}, {""text"": ""and several big draws are possible,
the pre-flop raiser might just check back."", ""start"": 282.366, ""duration"": 4.561}, {""text"": ""There are situations where 
donk-betting can be effective:"", ""start"": 287.027, ""duration"": 3.013}, {""text"": ""denying free cards and making
 your opponent pay to continue."", ""start"": 290.14, ""duration"": 3.49}, {""text"": ""As always, you can do this for value
 or you can do it as a bluff..."", ""start"": 293.73, ""duration"": 3.867}, {""text"": ""if you think your opponents 
are likely to fold."", ""start"": 297.647, ""duration"": 2.153}, {""text"": ""Even more exciting and threatening,
however, is the check-raise -"", ""start"": 301.35, ""duration"": 3.95}, {""text"": ""Checking when the action's on you 
only to raise after a player..."", ""start"": 305.4, ""duration"": 3.679}, {""text"": ""behind you has bet."", ""start"": 309.179, ""duration"": 1.399}, {""text"": ""This completely shakes up
 the order of things and strikes..."", ""start"": 310.628, ""duration"": 3.572}, {""text"": ""fear into the C-betting player,
who might have been caught bluffing."", ""start"": 314.25, ""duration"": 3.771}, {""text"": ""Now you know about 
various betting tactics,"", ""start"": 318.071, ""duration"": 2.729}, {""text"": ""you'll want to know about sizing
your post-flop bets."", ""start"": 320.8, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""And as is so often the case, it
comes down to position,"", ""start"": 325.55, ""duration"": 3.55}, {""text"": ""community cards, and the other players 
at the table."", ""start"": 329.2, ""duration"": 2.425}, {""text"": ""But here are a few general guidelines..."", ""start"": 331.775, ""duration"": 2.451}, {""text"": ""On a dry board with few, if any, draws
 possible, you don't have to bet very big at all."", ""start"": 334.676, ""duration"": 5.324}, {""text"": ""Because your opponent either 
has it or they don't."", ""start"": 340.05, ""duration"": 2.719}, {""text"": ""25% to 30% of what's already in the
 middle is fine here."", ""start"": 342.869, ""duration"": 3.623}, {""text"": ""If your opponent calls, there's a reasonable
 chance they've connected with the board."", ""start"": 346.592, ""duration"": 3.892}, {""text"": ""You can use that information:
 whether it means continuing to..."", ""start"": 350.584, ""duration"": 2.764}, {""text"": ""bet for value or putting the
 brakes on your bluffing plans."", ""start"": 353.448, ""duration"": 4.157}, {""text"": ""On a wet board, with draws aplenty, 
you might not be betting to bluff at all."", ""start"": 357.655, ""duration"": 4.445}, {""text"": ""But where you have the best hand
and want to keep it that way,"", ""start"": 362.35, ""duration"": 3.192}, {""text"": ""you should be betting more."", ""start"": 365.592, ""duration"": 1.108}, {""text"": ""If there's a possible straight
draw, 50% of the pot or a little over..."", ""start"": 366.9, ""duration"": 3.6}, {""text"": ""that amount will be a good 
value bet."", ""start"": 370.55, ""duration"": 1.55}, {""text"": ""On a very wet board with straights
and flushes in view,"", ""start"": 372.5, ""duration"": 3.5}, {""text"": ""that should creep up to 75% or 80%."", ""start"": 376.1, ""duration"": 2.803}, {""text"": ""Against players you know to
 be weak,"", ""start"": 378.953, ""duration"": 2.447}, {""text"": ""who don't have any real 
understanding of odds,"", ""start"": 381.45, ""duration"": 2.15}, {""text"": ""you can opt to bump up those bets
 to 90 or even 100% of the pot..."", ""start"": 383.85, ""duration"": 4.902}, {""text"": ""to get even more value."", ""start"": 388.802, ""duration"": 1.498}, {""text"": ""So, those are the basics of betting
and raising from PokerStars."", ""start"": 390.7, ""duration"": 4.1}, {""text"": ""Don't forget to give us a like,
and subscribe for more poker videos."", ""start"": 395.25, ""duration"": 3.2}, {""text"": ""Also, leave us a comment, let us know
 which poker lesson you'd like to see next."", ""start"": 398.55, ""duration"": 4.314}, {""text"": ""I'm James Hartigan. Thanks for watching."", ""start"": 402.914, ""duration"": 1.586}]"

cards, depends on a..."", ""start"": 13.85, ""duration"": 2.638}, {""text"": ""combination of things."", ""start"": 16.588, ""duration"": 0.731}, {""text"": ""In this video, I will break down
 starting hands into different categories,"", ""start"": 17.419, ""duration"": 3.763}, {""text"": ""and offer some advice on the types of 
hands you should be playing,"", ""start"": 21.282, ""duration"": 3.418}, {""text"": ""while also explaining how your position 
at the table and the players you're..."", ""start"": 24.8, ""duration"": 3.557}, {""text"": ""competing against might impact
 your decision."", ""start"": 28.407, ""duration"": 2.493}, {""text"": ""Don't forget: for more poker tutorials
and the best poker content on YouTube,"", ""start"": 30.95, ""duration"": 4.462}, {""text"": ""hit the subscribe button."", ""start"": 35.462, ""duration"": 1.338}, {""text"": ""So, how do you decide whether to
play the two cards you've been dealt?"", ""start"": 40.05, ""duration"": 3.777}, {""text"": ""Well, it's all about the strength 
of these cards."", ""start"": 43.877, ""duration"": 2.123}, {""text"": ""This will determine whether you
should be getting involved and..."", ""start"": 46.4, ""duration"": 2.5}, {""text"": ""putting any chips into the pot."", ""start"": 48.95, ""duration"": 2.264}, {""text"": ""Yes, there are more cards to be revealed 
which will change things,"", ""start"": 51.314, ""duration"": 3.573}, {""text"": ""but here is a hashtag #FunFact."", ""start"": 54.937, ""duration"": 2.063}, {""text"": ""A strong starting hand will win against
a weaker one three times out of four."", ""start"": 57.05, ""duration"": 4.586}, {""text"": ""And when you're beginning
 your poker journey..."", ""start"": 61.686, ""duration"": 2.114}, {""text"": ""a really solid strategy is to focus
on just playing strong hands."", ""start"": 63.8, ""duration"": 4.1}, {""text"": ""So, what are you looking for?"", ""start"": 68.2, ""duration"": 2.345}, {""text"": ""The best starting hands are the 'Monsters.'
Big pairs: Aces, Kings, and Queens,"", ""start"": 70.645, ""duration"": 6.292}, {""text"": ""plus Ace-King."", ""start"": 76.987, ""duration"": 1.413}, {""text"": ""Very good hands are Jacks, Tens, 
and Nines, plus Ace-Queen, Ace-Jack,"", ""start"": 79.25, ""duration"": 5.483}, {""text"": ""Ace-Ten, and King-Queen."", ""start"": 85.233, ""duration"": 1.681}, {""text"": ""All other pairs are decent. 
As are suited Aces."", ""start"": 87.014, ""duration"": 4.569}, {""text"": ""For example, Ace-Five of clubs."", ""start"": 91.633, ""duration"": 2.167}, {""text"": ""Other hands that fall into the decent
category include combinations of high cards,"", ""start"": 93.85, ""duration"": 4.3}, {""text"": ""like King-Jack, Queen-Jack, 
and Jack 10 plus so-called suited connectors."", ""start"": 98.25, ""duration"": 5.217}, {""text"": ""For example, Six-Five of diamonds 
and Eight-Seven of spades."", ""start"": 103.517, ""duration"": 4.483}, {""text"": ""With this type of starting hand,"", ""start"": 108.2, ""duration"": 1.5}, {""text"": ""You have the chance to make a straight
or a flush, or even a straight flush..."", ""start"": 109.75, ""duration"": 4.75}, {""text"": ""but probably only if you're James Bond."", ""start"": 114.55, ""duration"": 2.05}, {""text"": ""There are some situations where
you might find yourself playing...."", ""start"": 116.75, ""duration"": 4.2}, {""text"": ""'Speculative' hands: non-suited connectors, 
for example, Ten-Nine,"", ""start"": 121.05, ""duration"": 3.581}, {""text"": ""or not quite connected cards:
one-gappers like Ten-Eight of hearts."", ""start"": 124.731, ""duration"": 4.464}, {""text"": ""But pretty much everything
else falls into the trash category."", ""start"": 129.245, ""duration"": 4.255}, {""text"": ""They're really not playable at
all in Hold'em. So fold them."", ""start"": 133.6, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""The worst starting hand is 
Seven-Two off-suit."", ""start"": 137.05, ""duration"": 2.65}, {""text"": ""It doesn't have a realistic chance
of making a straight or a..."", ""start"": 139.8, ""duration"": 2.6}, {""text"": ""...flush and neither card is high."", ""start"": 142.45, ""duration"": 2.31}, {""text"": ""Okay. We've sorted the good
 from the bad."", ""start"": 144.86, ""duration"": 3.052}, {""text"": ""However, it's important to 
remember your position at the table..."", ""start"": 148.012, ""duration"": 3.36}, {""text"": ""massively influences which 
hand you should be playing."", ""start"": 151.422, ""duration"": 2.678}, {""text"": ""As a rule of thumb, the more players
still to act the better..."", ""start"": 155.7, ""duration"": 3.5}, {""text"": ""your starting hand needs to be,
because there's a higher chance..."", ""start"": 159.2, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""of someone behind you having a
monster."", ""start"": 162.4, ""duration"": 1.9}, {""text"": ""So generally speaking, stick to
playing really strong hands in..."", ""start"": 164.6, ""duration"": 3.9}, {""text"": ""early position where you're
one of the first players to act,"", ""start"": 168.5, ""duration"": 2.6}, {""text"": ""and save the decent and speculative
hands for when you're in late position."", ""start"": 171.3, ""duration"": 4.6}, {""text"": ""When you're one of the last players
to act and you've seen what..."", ""start"": 176.0, ""duration"": 2.9}, {""text"": ""your opponents have decided to do."", ""start"": 178.9, ""duration"": 1.7}, {""text"": ""It's important to observe the table
you're at and adjust accordingly."", ""start"": 183.3, ""duration"": 2.9}, {""text"": ""Really tight tables where players
wait for premium cards,"", ""start"": 186.7, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""and therefore play fewer hands
are going to allow you to..."", ""start"": 189.75, ""duration"": 2.903}, {""text"": ""play a little looser, 
open up your game,"", ""start"": 192.703, ""duration"": 2.097}, {""text"": ""maybe even giving you the
 opportunity to raise with..."", ""start"": 195.1, ""duration"": 2.509}, {""text"": ""small pairs and connectors 
in early position."", ""start"": 197.659, ""duration"": 1.941}, {""text"": ""Tight players are likely to fold your
raises a lot of the time,"", ""start"": 199.8, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""allowing you to steal lots of small
pots. But on the flip side,"", ""start"": 203.0, ""duration"": 3.9}, {""text"": ""to win a really loose table like
 the ones often found at..."", ""start"": 207.05, ""duration"": 3.217}, {""text"": ""lower stakes, you'll need to play tighter,"", ""start"": 210.417, ""duration"": 2.439}, {""text"": ""waiting for strong hands
and raising in late position."", ""start"": 212.906, ""duration"": 3.188}, {""text"": ""Loose players get involved
 in too many hands."", ""start"": 216.144, ""duration"": 2.756}, {""text"": ""You can exploit this with patience."", ""start"": 218.9, ""duration"": 2.2}, {""text"": ""Eventually your monster will blow
their trash out of the water."", ""start"": 221.3, ""duration"": 3.8}, {""text"": ""You will find a link below to download
some charts."", ""start"": 225.35, ""duration"": 3.068}, {""text"": ""They'll help you understand 
which starting hands..."", ""start"": 228.468, ""duration"": 2.132}, {""text"": ""you should be playing from which
position."", ""start"": 230.65, ""duration"": 2.35}, {""text"": ""Major caveat: 
This is purely a recommendation,"", ""start"": 233.05, ""duration"": 3.55}, {""text"": ""not a guaranteed recipe for success."", ""start"": 236.65, ""duration"": 2.032}, {""text"": ""Well, I hope you've enjoyed this video

What hands should you  "", ""start"": 98.52, ""duration"": 6.18}, {""text"": ""play? And the answer is actually you should only play aces. Because if you only play aces and you  "", ""start"": 104.7, ""duration"": 6.72}, {""text"": ""go all in, once like anybody's raised, you go all in with aces you can never lose."", ""start"": 111.42, ""duration"": 4.32}, {""text"": ""Because you're never forced to put in money unless you're going all in with the best hand."", ""start"": 115.74, ""duration"": 3.54}, {""text"": ""So really the reason we play hands is all about the blinds and when people are playing a bunch of  "", ""start"": 120.24, ""duration"": 5.22}, {""text"": ""hands, it costs you so little in comparison to the size of the pots to just wait for better hands-"", ""start"": 125.46, ""duration"": 6.06}, {""text"": ""and enter the pot with better hands, so that's ""hack"", tip number one is, play tight, play  "", ""start"": 132.12, ""duration"": 6.6}, {""text"": ""good hands. Number two is, fast play your good hands. Number three,"", ""start"": 208.62, ""duration"": 4.2}, {""text"": ""figure out when people have to have a made hand. And so what I mean by that is, you raise in early"", ""start"": 214.68, ""duration"": 8.82}, {""text"": ""position, the button calls, the big blind calls, the flop is; king, 7, 3, rainbow, check, you bet half"", ""start"": 223.5, ""duration"": 9.12}, {""text"": ""pot the button calls and the big blind folds. "[{""text"": ""Hello, welcome to PokerStars Learn."", ""start"": 0.3, ""duration"": 1.9}, {""text"": ""I'm James Hartigan and this is

 start your poker journey."", ""start"": 5.74, ""duration"": 3.243}, {""text"": ""After watching this video,"", ""start"": 9.033, ""duration"": 1.267}, {""text"": ""you will know the basics and be
able to play your first hand of poker."", ""start"": 10.4, ""duration"": 3.7}, {""text"": ""And if you want to learn more, please
 don't forget to subscribe to our channel."", ""start"": 14.5, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""So, when we talk about poker, the
most popular version of the game -"", ""start"": 20.0, ""duration"": 2.8}, {""text"": ""which you see in movies, on TV, and
on live streams -"", ""start"": 22.85, ""duration"": 3.197}, {""text"": ""is No Limit Texas Hold'em,"", ""start"": 26.097, ""duration"": 1.303}, {""text"": ""and that's what we are going to
learn to play in this video."", ""start"": 27.4, ""duration"": 2.4}, {""text"": ""The aim of Texas Hold'em is simple:
make the best five-card poker hand..."", ""start"": 30.25, ""duration"": 3.85}, {""text"": ""from the two cards you've been dealt 
and the five shared cards..."", ""start"": 34.2, ""duration"": 3.28}, {""text"": ""in the middle of the table."", ""start"": 37.58, ""duration"": 1.578}, {""text"": ""Or act like you have the best
 five-card hand!"", ""start"": 39.258, ""duration"": 2.645}, {""text"": ""So what beats what? Well, let's run
 through the official hand"", ""start"": 42.053, ""duration"": 2.881}, {""text"": ""rankings, starting at the bottom
 and work your way to the top."", ""start"": 44.984, ""duration"": 3.516}, {""text"": ""The worst you can have is a high
card. No two cards are the same,"", ""start"": 48.95, ""duration"": 3.503}, {""text"": ""and the five cards don't connect
 in any other way."", ""start"": 52.503, ""duration"": 2.497}, {""text"": ""Ideally, you'd like to have at least
one pair: two cards of the same value."", ""start"": 55.65, ""duration"": 4.325}, {""text"": ""Aces are the highest pair. A pair of twos
 is the lowest."", ""start"": 60.075, ""duration"": 3.926}, {""text"": ""Two pair is better. Pretty self-explanatory."", ""start"": 64.675, ""duration"": 1.978}, {""text"": ""In this example, a pair of Kings 
and a pair of Sixes."", ""start"": 66.753, ""duration"": 3.748}, {""text"": ""Three-of-a-kind is also pretty 
self-explanatory, and it beats two pair."", ""start"": 70.651, ""duration"": 5.074}, {""text"": ""Next up, a straight: Five cards
 in a row of different suits."", ""start"": 75.825, ""duration"": 4.775}, {""text"": ""An ace can be high or low but
no wraparounds are allowed."", ""start"": 80.85, ""duration"": 4.464}, {""text"": ""Queen-King-Ace-Two-Three
 is not a hand!"", ""start"": 85.364, ""duration"": 3.336}, {""text"": ""Then a flush: Five cards of the
same suit, doesn't matter what..."", ""start"": 89.4, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""order they're in."", ""start"": 92.6, ""duration"": 1.015}, {""text"": ""A full house  - also known as a boat -
It's where you have three-of-a-kind plus a pair,"", ""start"": 93.715, ""duration"": 4.888}, {""text"": ""That is a very strong hand, but it's
still beaten by quads,"", ""start"": 98.703, ""duration"": 4.148}, {""text"": ""officially known as four-of-a-kind."", ""start"": 102.901, ""duration"": 2.399}, {""text"": ""A straight flush is an incredibly
rare hand."", ""start"": 106.35, ""duration"": 2.781}, {""text"": ""Five cards in a row, all of the 
same suit."", ""start"": 109.231, ""duration"": 3.291}, {""text"": ""And the Royal Flush is unbeatable.
 It's a straight flush - Ten to the Ace."", ""start"": 112.572, ""duration"": 4.628}, {""text"": ""Please note your chances of being
dealt this hand are roughly 30,000 to 1!"", ""start"": 117.5, ""duration"": 5.1}, {""text"": ""And those are the hand rankings.
To recap: It goes high card, one pair,"", ""start"": 122.95, ""duration"": 5.765}, {""text"": ""two pair, three-of-a-kind,
 a straight, a flush, a full house,"", ""start"": 128.999, ""duration"": 4.701}, {""text"": ""four-of-a-kind, straight flush, 
and the Royal Flush."", ""start"": 133.95, ""duration"": 3.079}, {""text"": ""There's also a downloadable hand
rankings guide in the description."", ""start"": 137.079, ""duration"": 4.421}, {""text"": ""This is really useful to have by
your side for easy reference,"", ""start"": 141.6, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""when you're starting to play the
game."", ""start"": 144.95, ""duration"": 2.269}, {""text"": ""So, how does a hand of 
poker play out?"", ""start"": 147.269, ""duration"": 2.931}, {""text"": ""Let's start with three important
positions at the table..."", ""start"": 150.5, ""duration"": 3.325}, {""text"": ""The button, sometimes referred to
as the dealer button,"", ""start"": 153.925, ""duration"": 2.936}, {""text"": ""and to their immediate left, the small 
blind and the big blind."", ""start"": 156.961, ""duration"": 3.895}, {""text"": ""Before any cards are dealt,
they have to put chips in, they are..."", ""start"": 160.956, ""duration"": 3.508}, {""text"": ""literally forced to bet blind. 
Hence, the name."", ""start"": 164.514, ""duration"": 2.786}, {""text"": ""the player in the big blind posts
the current minimum bet,"", ""start"": 167.95, ""duration"": 2.792}, {""text"": ""with the player in the small blind -
 to their right - posting half that amount."", ""start"": 170.792, ""duration"": 4.108}, {""text"": ""The cards will then be dealt in
a clockwise order, starting with..."", ""start"": 175.4, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""the player to the left of the button.
Now, if you play online or at a casino,"", ""start"": 178.7, ""duration"": 4.9}, {""text"": ""you won't have to worry about dealing."", ""start"": 183.6, ""duration"": 1.4}, {""text"": ""But if your playing privately with
friends, it's standard for the..."", ""start"": 185.0, ""duration"": 2.6}, {""text"": ""player with the dealer button to
actually deal the hand."", ""start"": 187.6, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""Once everyone has been dealt two
cards, known as their 'hole cards,'"", ""start"": 191.4, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""it's time for the first betting
round."", ""start"": 194.55, ""duration"": 1.829}, {""text"": ""Now, because the players in the 
small blind and big blind have...."", ""start"": 196.429, ""duration"": 2.571}, {""text"": ""already been forced to bet, the action
 starts with the player to their left."", ""start"": 199.2, ""duration"": 4.8}, {""text"": ""This player has a decision to make
based on the two cards they've been dealt."", ""start"": 204.0, ""duration"": 4.4}, {""text"": ""They can fold and wait for the
next hand,"", ""start"": 208.7, ""duration"": 2.1}, {""text"": ""but if they want to stay in, they
can 'call', in other words, match..."", ""start"": 211.1, ""duration"": 3.8}, {""text"": ""the amount of the big blind,"", ""start"": 214.95, ""duration"": 1.863}, {""text"": ""or they can raise and 
set a new bet..."", ""start"": 216.863, ""duration"": 2.137}, {""text"": ""that every other player has to
match."", ""start"": 219.0, ""duration"": 2.0}, {""text"": ""The minimum raise is double the
big blind. And the maximum?"", ""start"": 221.25, ""duration"": 3.708}, {""text"": ""Well, it depends on the 
type of game,"", ""start"": 225.008, ""duration"": 1.692}, {""text"": ""but if you're playing No Limit,
there isn't a maximum!"", ""start"": 226.75, ""duration"": 3.021}, {""text"": ""At any point a player can go 
'all in' and bet everything..."", ""start"": 229.871, ""duration"": 3.509}, {""text"": ""in front of them."", ""start"": 233.43, ""duration"": 0.87}, {""text"": ""If a player raises and everybody
else folds, the hand is over."", ""start"": 234.8, ""duration"": 3.3}, {""text"": ""But for the sake of argument, let's
assume someone raises and..."", ""start"": 238.3, ""duration"": 3.0}, {""text"": ""one or more players match
 this bet."", ""start"": 241.3, ""duration"": 1.9}, {""text"": ""That means we move to the next
round and we get to see the 'flop:'"", ""start"": 251.1, ""duration"": 4.1}, {""text"": ""three cards dealt face-up in the
middle of the table."", ""start"": 255.5, ""duration"": 2.503}, {""text"": ""These are often referred to as
community cards, because..."", ""start"": 258.75, ""duration"": 3.247}, {""text"": ""they are shared by all the players."", ""start"": 261.997, ""duration"": 2.003}, {""text"": ""So, everyone now has a five-card poker

 betting round."", ""start"": 269.2, ""duration"": 2.3}, {""text"": ""The action starts with the first

but I'm staying in the hand."", ""start"": 292.483, ""duration"": 3.017}, {""text"": ""I'm passing the action along to
the next player and I will react..."", ""start"": 295.6, ""duration"": 3.2}, {""text"": ""to whatever they decide to do."", ""start"": 298.8, ""duration"": 1.6}, {""text"": ""'Bet' means I'm putting chips into
the pot."", ""start"": 301.25, ""duration"": 3.283}, {""text"": ""'Call' means I'm matching the bet."", ""start"": 304.683, ""duration"": 2.573}, {""text"": ""'Raise' means I'm increasing 
the size of the bet."", ""start"": 307.356, ""duration"": 3.845}, {""text"": ""And 'fold' means I don't want

 choose from when trying..."", ""start"": 333.871, ""duration"": 3.438}, {""text"": ""to make a good five-card

 betting before the 'river' card..."", ""start"": 340.2, ""duration"": 3.527}, {""text"": ""is dealt face-up next to the

available to them."", ""start"": 347.3, ""duration"": 3.1}, {""text"": ""Remember the aim of the game is

else's, you win all the chips in the pot."", ""start"": 374.3, ""duration"": 4.9}, {""text"": ""Once a hand is over, the dealer button
